The Nasarawa State Police Command has confirmed the death of a young man, identified as James Samuel. The farmer hanged himself in the school he had his secondary education. Samuel, 30, took his life in a classroom at Government Secondary School, Gurku in the Karu LGA. Police Public Relations Officer, Mr. Ramhan Nansel, confirmed the development in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Saturday. The man was confirmed dead by a doctor at the Mararaba Medical Centre in Karu. “The incident happened in the early hours of this morning. He hanged himself in a classroom. The police visited the scene and have taken his body to the hospital where he was confirmed dead by the doctor on duty.” Nansel assured that the command had commenced on the incident.